for the national endowment for the arts 
were spending 175 million in this area that benefits 
primarily the rich and the perverted the rev donald wildmon 
founder and director of the tupelo missbased association said 
wednesday 
but barry blinderman director of the galleries said the 
exhibitions beneficiaries were the 6000 students and middleclass 
residents of normal ill who turned up 
the show received excellent local coverage and the support of 
a supposedly conservative media here he said 
