projects held by a prominent democratic fundraiser have financial 
or physical problems a top federal housing official says 
francis a keating general counsel of the department of housing 
and urban development defended on wednesday the departments 
suspension last january of a bruce rozet from hud contracts over 
concerns about management of a handful of projects with which he 
was connected 
keating acknowledged to a house subcommittee that hud took the 
action based on evidence involving only a small number of 
properties 
but he said the troubled projects were symptomatic of larger 
problems involving rozets web of affiliated corporate entities 
