the company contends that the potential worldwide market for the 
product is 1 billion annually and that it has been barred from 
japan because the japanese government wanted to foster development 
of a rival amorphous metal product 
in announcing her decision hills said she would expedite review 
of a new petition from allied signal seeking retaliation if the 
talks over the next 150 days fail to resolve the dispute 
allied signal chairman edward l hennessy jr said he accepted 
the administrations decision to negotiate in light of recent 
actions by japan to lower barriers to foreign products 
the recently announced progress in the trade talks between the 
united states and japan holds out the promise that trade issues 
between the two nations can be resolved in a more businesslike and 
less confrontational manner he said in a statement 
sen john danforth a leading congressional critic of japan 
said the administration would have to be dogged in its pursuit 
of a successful resolution of the dispute 
the bottom line has to be results in the form of export sales 
for a us firm that is being shut out by japan danforth rmo 
said in statement 
</TEXT>
