dealers said the dollars slide in tokyo followed its overnight 
downswing in new york despite a report wednesday of a sharp 
improvement in the us merchandise trade figures for february 
japanese investors had bought the dollar earlier based on 
their expectation that the us trade deficit would largely 
improve and then they dumped the currency when the figure actually 
came out said mitsuhiko kinugasa a dealer with daiwa bank 
