supplydemand balance in the dairy markets 
milk production has resumed expansion and falling 
international prices of nonfat dry milk have demolished 
opportunities for commercial exports the report said 
but domestic demand has been strong both commercially and to 
rebuild depleted inventories 
milk prices at the farm probably will slip in the coming months 
and the onset of seasonal increases may be delayed the report 
said overall the farm price of milk in 1990 may average 4 percent 
