hundredweight 
consumer prices of dairy products as a group in early 1990 had 
risen more than 10 percent from a year earlier greatly exceeding 
the overall increases in retail food and consumer prices 
retail dairy prices probably will trend down in coming months 
although any signs of strength in wholesale prices will tend to 
lessen and delay retail price declines the report said 
