control data corp has reached a 
tentative deal to sell vtc inc its moneylosing computer chip 
subsidiary to seattle silicon of bellevue wash 
under the proposed agreement seattle silicon would buy the 
assets of vtc in order to form a new company that hasnt been named 
control data would hold a 20 percent stake in the new company 
which would be headed by amaury piedra seattle silicons president 
and chief executive officer 
terms of the proposed agreement announced wednesday were not 
announced 
the new company would continue to operate vtcs bloomington 
plant and keep nearly all of vtcs 400 employees said ed 
fernandez vice president of marketing and sales for seattle 
silicon 
larry jodsaas president of vtc will stay with control data in 
an undetermined position said control data spokesman frank ryan 
expecting to sell vtc control data took a 110 million charge 
against its earnings last year control data lost 6804 million 
last year and has sold or closed several operations in an attempt 
to achieve a turnaround 
vtc is certainly the last obstacle to remove in the 
restructuring of control data said nancy foltz a control data 
spokeswoman it was the only remaining business that consistently 
lost money 
control data does not provide financial information on vtc 
which designs computer chips for the military and the disk drive 
data storage industry 
seattle silicon is a private 6yearold chip maker that has not 
had its own manufacturing facility it has been making chips 
through alliances with other companies 
in december control data reached agreement to sell its 
ticketron division which provides tickets to theaters concerts 
and sports events through a computer network 
terms of the deal were not disclosed 
the buyers were a group consisting of centre group lp of 
landover md ogden allied services corp of new york wembley 
