the cost of a radisson hotel room in knoxville tenn has gone 
up by 5 the soupandsalad bar tab at an indianapolis howard 
johnsons restaurant jumped 29 percent and the peddie school in 
heightstown nj is hiking tuition and room and board 1500 per 
student in the coming academic year 
a slowing overall economy has helped curb some inflation but 
price increases in the service sector spurred by higher wages 
skyrocketing insurance costs and a shortage of workers are 
leaving no american wallet untouched 
were all paying a little more said james f smith a 
finance professor at the university of north carolina 
recent government figures sent mixed signals about inflation 
the price of finished goods slipped 02 percent in march and 
further declines in food and energy prices should keep wholesale 
inflation below last years rate but consumer prices jumped an 
unexpected 05 percent last month the equivalent of an 85 
percent annual inflation rate 
economists agree that the service sector accounts for the 
divergence the cost of services are factored into consumer prices 
but are not a component of the governments producer price index 
it seems that the majority of americans are employed in the 
service sector and thats why inflation seems to be bigger 
problem said marc chandler an analyst at mms international in 
chicago 
some parts of the service sector have dramatically improved 
their efficiency especially banking retailing and other 
businesses that have benefited from the information revolution 
which lowered costs through automation smith said 
but a shortage of workers in several regions of the country and 
the first increase in the minimum wage in nearly a decade are 
pumping wages higher 
while only about 3 million americans earn the minimum wage 
which increased april 1 to 380 an hour from 335 it sets a 
floor for other lowerpaying jobs 
