some energy analysts regarded the opec announcement as a ploy to 
keep prices from falling further in hopes that a seasonal rise in 
gasoline demand will sop up the crude oil surplus eliminating the 
need for a cut in opec production quotas 
basically this is a little bit of a stability conspiracy 
said peter beutel the head of energy trading for elders futures 
inc 
