outside the windows of the federal bankruptcy 
courthouse the fading sun reddened the sky over new york harbor 
inside the sun was setting on frank lorenzos reign over 
eastern airlines 
david i shapiro the courtappointed examiner for eastern had 
remained uncharacteristically quiet through most of the fourday 
hearing over a request by creditors to put an outside trustee in 
charge of the airline now at around 720 pm wednesday all the 
witnesses had been heard and shapiro let loose 
the issue in this case is 12 billion in losses within a 
year thundered shapiro a bear of a man known as a tough 
mediator can mr lorenzo now be allowed to wipe out the 
creditors interest can anyone blame the creditors for being 
outraged 
the 100 or so people packed into the small courtroom of us 
bankruptcy judge burton r lifland hung on every word attorneys 
for easterns unions which shut down the airline in march 1989 
