<TEXT>
here is a list of some leading american corporations and 
examples of what they say they are doing as part of their 
sensitivity and commitment to the environment 
amana has developed a companywide employee recycling program 
for newspapers plastic jugs and motor oil all proceeds from sales 
of recycled material will be donated to a nonprofit environmental 
group 
amoco chemical has reduced disposal of hazardous waste by 87 
percent 
arco chemical has promoted the antifreeze agent propylene 
glycol over the more toxic ethlyene glycol 
du pont plans to reduce air emissions by 60 percent in three 
years and is developing alternatives to chlorofluorocarbons oil 
subsidiary conoco has ordered two doublehulled tankers and plans 
to add more 
eaton has promoted use of recycling and reduction of hazardous 
wastes in its manufacturing processes 
general electric is evaluating products based on their 
environmental impact and plans to invest 200 million in 
environmental projects this year 
general mills has required use of recycled papers in all cereal 
boxboard and has banned use of heavy metals in printing inks 
general motors has announced intent to massproduce an electric 
car 
hj heinz has developed easyrecycling ketchup bottles and 
pledged not to buy tuna caught by fisherman who trapped dolphins 
ibm has achieved 84 percent recycle rate for hazardous waste 
and reduced chlorofluorocarbon emissions by at least 25 percent 
plans to recycle 50 percent of solid waste by 992 and eliminate cfc 
emissions by 1993 
johnson amp johnson has announced expanded companywide recycling 
program that originates at the employees desk and eliminated use 
of styrofoam cups in the workplace 
kodak plans to recycle disposable cameras and is spending more 
than 140 million to improve chemical storage and slash toxic 
emissions by 1995 
mcdonalds has cut 1 million pounds of waste by shortening 
straws and uses recycled paper for napkins and trays has pledged 
to use recycled products in at least 25 percent of annual 
expenditures on restaurant construction and equipment 
monsanto has pledged to cut hazardous air emissions at plants 
worldwide by 90 percent by 1992 and will spend 600 million on 
environmental programs over the next two years 
pacific gas amp electric has joined with environmental groups to 
joint projects including a 10 million study of energy efficiency 
procter amp gamble has reduced the size of packaging components 
and is experimenting with the recycling of disposable diapers is 
marketing detergents in recycled plastic 
scott paper has sponsored plasticfoam recycling in washington 
and treeplanting campaigns plans to award highschool 
scholarships to students in scott communities who plan to pursue 
environmentrelated studies 
shell oil has promoted sales of a new environmentally 
enhanced gasoline that it says cuts emissions 
3m has pioneered a companywide effort to reduce solid and 
hazardous waste and announced plans to reduce all hazardous 
emissions by 90 percent 
union carbide recycles or reuses half its hazardous solid 
wastes and plans to spend 310 million over four years on the 
environment and recycling ventures 
</TEXT>
