<DOCNO> AP900419-0243 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
moodys investors service on thursday placed its 
ratings on citicorp shortterm and longterm debt under review for 
possible downgrade because of problems involving the banks real 
estate and third world loans 
the credit rating agency also said it was reviewing some ratings 
of citicorp subsidiaries including citibank na 
citicorp the nations largest banking company on tuesday 
reported that firstquarter earnings declined 56 percent 
predominantly because of problems associated with loans associated 
with a declining real estate market 
the move by moodys affects 31 billion in credit held by the 
parent company and 7 billion by subsidiaries 
moodys said the review will focus on the risks associated 
with citicorps high asset concentrations particularly 
commercial real estate highly leveraged transactions and third 
world loans 
citicorp is the nations largest lender for real estate some 
developers in regions of the country have been unable to repay 
loans to many banks because of a glut of new buildings that has 
caused prices to fall 
the review also will include an assessment of citicorps 
capital adequacy when adjusted for these risks as well as an 
evaluation of the outlook for the firms core profitability 
moodys said in a statement 
citicorp in the first quarter charged off 135 million of 
commercial loans in developing countries including 56 million of 
real estate loans mostly in north america also citicorp charged 
off about 40 million of loans to finance corporate takeovers or 
other heavily indebted borrowers 
in its statement moodys also said it would considser 
citicorps strengths which include an attractive and profitable 
consumer franchise and significant diversity in its business 
a credit downgrade could increase substantially the cost of 
borrowing for citicorp and its subsidiaries 
</TEXT>
