<TEXT>
knightridder inc posted a 25 percent increase in its 
firstquarter profit on thursday while affiliated publications 
inc said it had a profitable quarter in contrast to a loss in the 
same period a year ago 
a third media company pulitzer publishing co said its profit 
tumbled in the first three months of the year 
knightridder based in miami said it earned 258 million or 
50 cents per share in the three months ended march 31 compared 
with 205 million or 39 cents a share a year earlier 
firstquarter revenue rose 26 percent to 5549 million from 
5407 million 
the quarters results were favorably impacted by significantly 
lower newsprint prices lower interest costs a cut in our losses 
in detroit good performances from our business information 
services division and various joint ventures and approximately 
800000 fewer shares outstanding said senior vice president and 
chief financial officer robert f singleton 
the companys newspaper division posted lower earnings of 637 
million down from 646 million in the first quarter last year 
singleton said the calendar was partly to blame for lower 
earnings as rthere was one fewer sunday than a year ago 
the business information services division had an operating 
profit of 45 million up 313 percent over last years 34 
million 
knightridders interests include 29 daily newspapers business 
news and information services news graphics and photo services as 
well as cable television and newsprint manufacturing 
bostonbased affiliated publications which publishes the boston 
globe said it earned 65 million or 9 cents a share in the 
three months ended april 1 in contrast to a loss of 99 million 
or 14 cents a share in the sasme period in 1989 
revenue edged up to 1337 million from 1310 million a year 
ago 
the 1989 results reflected charges related to affiliateds share 
of losses from its former investment in mccaw cellular 
communications inc of kirkland wash the stake has since been 
sold 
despite the improvement the company said its results were 
adversely affected by softness in advertising volume at the globe 
affiliated publications is the parent company of the globe 
newspaper co and bpi communications inc a leading publisher of 
specialty magazines books and electronic data bases for the 
entertainment arts and design markets 
pulitzer publishing based in st louis mo blamed a 70 
percent decline in its firstquarter earnings on lower results at 
the st louis postdispatch and costs involved in the purchase of a 
new orleans television station 
the company reported earnings of 906000 or 9 cents per share 
on revenues of 95 million for the first quarter compared with 
earnings of 3 million or 29 cents per share on revenues of 94 
million a year ago 
the postdispatch is confronting the effects of expanded 
competition in a soft economy as well as difficult labor 
negotiations said chairman joseph pulitzer jr 
the decreased earnings also reflect costs connected with the 
acquisition of wdsutv in new orleans in december 
pulitzers newspaper operations include two major metropolitan 
dailies the postdispatch and the arizona daily star in tucson 
and newspapers and shoppers in the chicago area including the 
southtown economist a suburban daily and sunday newspaper 
pulitzers broadcasting operations consist of seven 
networkaffilitated television stations wyff in greenville sc 
weal in lancaster pa wxii in winstonsalem nc koat in 
albuquerque nm ketv in omaha neb wlky in louisville ky 
and wdsu in new orleans pulitzer also owns radio stations ktaram 
and kkltfm in phoenix 
